---
/**
 * PainSection.astro
 *
 * Pain agitation section for Duka Masonry.
 * Goes 3 layers deep: the visible problem → the hidden damage → the cost of waiting.
 * Follows the PAS framework to create urgency without being pushy.
 */
---

<section class="bg-offwhite text-charcoal py-20">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-16">
      <p class="text-gold text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Sound Familiar?</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold leading-snug">
        Most homeowners ignore masonry damage until it becomes a much bigger problem.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- 3-layer pain grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

      <!-- Layer 1: Surface pain — visible problem -->
      <div class="border-t-4 border-gold pt-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-gold mb-3">Layer 1 — What You See</p>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">A crack here. A gap there. Bricks that look wrong.</h3>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed">
          Maybe it's a chimney that's been shedding pieces. A retaining wall that's starting to lean.
          Mortar joints so eroded you can scrape them out with your fingernail.
          You know something's off — you've just been hoping it'll hold a little longer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 2: Hidden damage -->
      <div class="border-t-4 border-charcoal pt-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 mb-3">Layer 2 — What You Can't See</p>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Water is already inside — and it's spreading.</h3>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed">
          Every open crack is a doorway for water. It seeps behind your walls, under your slab,
          into your chimney lining. You won't notice the mold or the rotting framing until
          a contractor tears something open. By then, what started as a masonry issue
          is now a structural one.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 3: Cost of waiting -->
      <div class="border-t-4 border-charcoal pt-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 mb-3">Layer 3 — What It's Costing You</p>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Every CT winter makes it worse — and more expensive.</h3>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70 leading-relaxed">
          Water gets in, freezes, and expands. That tiny crack becomes a fracture.
          That loose stone becomes a collapse. A $400 repointing job you put off for a year
          can turn into a $4,000 rebuild. The damage isn't waiting for you to be ready.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Bridge to solution -->
    <div class="mt-14 bg-charcoal text-offwhite px-8 py-6 max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold leading-relaxed">
        The good news: most masonry damage is very fixable — if you catch it early.
        Duka Masonry gives you a straight diagnosis and an honest quote. No upselling. No guesswork.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
